80,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"5770ebd8-a541-0492-ea42-3f9fd59b7295","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute HMAC Signature\n\nComputes the HMAC-SHA256 of the raw payload to verify the sender's signature before trusting the data.\n\nNext: Signature Valid?","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"4385c7c9-70d0-1d0a-73a6-d1b983a5ee13","name":"Note: Compute HMAC Signature"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Signature Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.computedSignature === $json.headers['x-signature']`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Map to Canonical Schema · ②→ Reject (HTTP 401)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"cb18ceb7-cede-4be6-df71-d2def8bb4de1","name":"Note: Signature Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Reject (HTTP 401)\n\nSends the HTTP 401 response back to the caller — keep this fast; heavy work happens after/async.","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,1000],"id":"74d46019-18c1-1f8e-43fc-41828548cdb0","name":"Note: Reject (HTTP 401)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Map to Canonical Schema\n\nShapes the item: writes `jobId`, `kind`, `payload`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Route by Event Kind","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,520],"id":"ba1ac090-b9ad-c8c7-198d-07b480ee64ac","name":"Note: Map to Canonical Schema"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Route by Event Kind\n\nRoutes each item to one of 3 lanes: created, updated + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Handle 'created' → Notion · ②→ Handle 'updated' → Forward API · ③→ Log Unrecognized Kind","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"12d6186e-0c2d-659b-b660-dcd47318c919","name":"Note: Route by Event Kind"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Handle 'created' → Notion\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,250],"id":"328ac668-4ceb-3e71-a676-74cba5280300","name":"Note: Handle 'created' → Notion"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Handle 'updated' → Forward API\n\nPOST https://api.example.com/v1/jobs — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,760],"id":"569a1f2f-f0dc-b0e0-1784-39a13855e6de","name":"Note: Handle 'updated' → Forward API"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Log Unrecognized Kind\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,1270],"id":"8a0a5e9b-59e9-2409-0811-df5226e19e1a","name":"Note: Log Unrecognized Kind"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Consolidate Handling\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Respond with Outcome","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,520],"id":"207c081a-33cf-995e-14c4-0105d3916646","name":"Note: Consolidate Handling"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Respond with Outcome\n\nSends the HTTP 200 response back to the caller — keep this fast; heavy work happens after/async.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"12070488-e3b7-f560-f04e-06e78addbe7c","name":"Note: Respond with Outcome"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per job (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"ac302b83-7b39-f4a2-f7a8-645d8e1f08c6","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"cf7a4551-68cc-8639-e065-f3b0d08160fb","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"f774affb-3360-1757-2990-1b779da45fe2","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"199c9a9f-fae8-92cb-ca60-a43c60aa9c05","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"7ffed518-5bdb-dcc6-13a5-1c687de3acdc","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"781b16e0-3365-4549-6b77-ed84a60397d6","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"8b03b56f-a4fe-16f0-4c19-5003bd719c80","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"a46fc2ee-a091-a720-8e64-fba9e3162216","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nReads every row from 'Job Tracker' — the read side of the store, e.g. for a digest or a downstream sync.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"b5d6b84e-fc03-c6af-50de-25c08865611a","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"671b5c89-44e9-99d8-2e33-8501deebf29a","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"33170c38-7200-d8cc-8688-77709dfa86bb","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Save Execution Metadata · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"b4138ed3-89ff-ad6a-2bd8-2cc2b06712b5","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty type","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"679485a9-3e2b-2c81-82a8-93b0f17a3461","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty type\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Sort Jobs Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"6747a7a2-90d0-2c34-b23e-c062360de7af","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty type"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Jobs Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,520],"id":"e9aa7f56-7e32-8e03-6658-a505603b345c","name":"Note: Sort Jobs Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,520],"id":"4dd46201-69df-8480-e2bd-fc49c804467e","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,520],"id":"69cef0ad-eca6-54ea-c086-ca4fd8033e72","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\nAppends a new row to 'Job Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,520],"id":"3302e58e-f73b-e484-dd06-42402e56b439","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#automation`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,520],"id":"833f93fc-54c3-e300-7559-e296efca4f4c","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Gmail","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,1540],"id":"fdaac073-8cb1-a1d2-2bfc-7de25ff46f25","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Gmail\n\nSends an email via Gmail — subject is the first line of the message body, recipient comes from the item's `email` field.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,1540],"id":"d6db978c-04f1-f542-9143-9cfea2609505","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Gmail"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,1540],"id":"abf04933-8e00-4009-c0d6-7bcf5febcb8a","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Notify the team on new events with Gmail end to end\n\n**Pattern:** Event Notification · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nNotify the team on new events with Gmail end to end. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual process orchestration is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Compute HMAC Signature → Signature Valid? → Map to Canonical Schema → Route by Event Kind → Handle 'created' → Notion → Consolidate Handling → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to event notification without manual effort\n- Anyone automating process orchestration in productivity\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"aa4df066-02f7-3d56-a3a0-f4c04217f8dc","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nThe optional HMAC check runs before any business logic touches the payload — bad signatures are rejected at the door rather than after work has already been done with untrusted data. Acking fast (HTTP 202) and doing the real work after the response is what stops the sender's webhook delivery from timing out and re-delivering the same event.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"e242e856-a499-be73-c1c8-0b1fc8917a21","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAbout as deep as this pattern goes — extend it:\n\n1. Turn on signature verification and trace what a tampered payload does at the 'Signature Valid?' gate.\n2. Add a new event kind to the switch and give it its own handler.\n3. Remove the fast-ack step and observe how response time changes under a slow downstream write.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"4021c0c6-cddf-6b3b-08a3-36c3c07b9aaf","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"ba1f67d2-2075-4f33-ee84-db2b477fdb10","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable, and the HMAC signature is verified before any processing. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"1913c2ee-32ad-9e08-66e9-b3ecdf30d948","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"1a3d0492-8046-03a4-5aa3-83efeaab3935","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your process orchestration process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-290],"id":"f116026f-fc76-74e2-cded-0961cf4cfd92","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute HMAC Signature","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute HMAC Signature":{"main":[[{"node":"Signature Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Signature Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Map to Canonical Schema","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Reject (HTTP 401)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Map to Canonical Schema":{"main":[[{"node":"Route by Event Kind","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Route by Event Kind":{"main":[[{"node":"Handle 'created' → Notion","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Handle 'updated' → Forward API","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Log Unrecognized Kind","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Handle 'created' → Notion":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Handle 'updated' → Forward API":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Log Unrecognized Kind":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Consolidate Handling":{"main":[[{"node":"Respond with Outcome","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Respond with Outcome":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty type","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty type":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Jobs Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Jobs Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Gmail","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Gmail":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1","saveDataErrorExecution":"all","saveManualExecutions":true,"executionTimeout":3600},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":[{"json":{"jobId":"JOB-4401","type":"export","payload":"customer-list-2026-07","status":"queued"}},{"json":{"jobId":"JOB-4402","type":"sync","payload":"inventory-delta","status":"running"}}]},"versionId":"91187769-6ba5-4a7e-ba45-fcf98ea6a7e9","id":"FDX06202"}